\b Theory:\b0\f1\par
Boolean retrieval model is a simple retrieval model based on set theory and boolean algebra. \par
Queries are designed as boolean expressions which have precise semantics. \par
A vector space model is a model where each term of the query is considered a vector dimension. \par
The TF-IDF value increases proportionally to the frequency a word appears in a document (TF) and is offset by the number of documents in the corpus that also contain that word (IDF).\par
